    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given block diagram</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbezcumy/0e04eff2-2b38-4c48-8a30-3cc81495525a/06c147a0-3fa1-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezcumz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbezcumy/0e04eff2-2b38-4c48-8a30-3cc81495525a/06c147a0-3fa1-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezcumz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>The signal flow graph representation of the block diagram is shown below,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf9242d/c548cb72-b3ef-488f-bf22-f45fa7cbfa0c/f76dd450-3fc6-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9242e.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf9242d/c548cb72-b3ef-488f-bf22-f45fa7cbfa0c/f76dd450-3fc6-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9242e.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>Forward path gain : $P_1=G_1, P_2=G_2$</p>\n<p>Individual loop gain : $L_1=-G_1$</p>\n<p>Number of two non-touching loops : 0</p>\n<p>Determinant</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta=1-L_1 \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left(-G_1\\right) \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1+G_1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(i) Path factor :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf94d6c/627ee0f3-a89a-4a04-8874-ad19371b363a/3615b740-3fc7-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf94d6d.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf94d6c/627ee0f3-a89a-4a04-8874-ad19371b363a/3615b740-3fc7-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf94d6d.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>Since, there is no loop, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_1=1-(\\text { isolated loop gain }) \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(ii)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf9cdx0/a6850315-f362-4e46-ac00-ceec6869ea61/15215340-3fc8-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9cdx1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf9cdx0/a6850315-f362-4e46-ac00-ceec6869ea61/15215340-3fc8-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9cdx1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 4\"></p>\n<p>Since, there is no loop, hence</p>\n<p>$\\Delta_2=1$-(Isolated loop gain)</p>\n<p>$\\Delta_2=1-0=1$</p>\n<p>Using Mason's gain formula, transfer function is given by,</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{C(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{1}{\\Delta} \\sum_k P_k \\Delta_k $$</p>\n<p>So, the transfer function is,</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1+G_1} $$</p>\n<p><b>From option (A) :</b></p>\n<p>The given signal flow graph</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf9f4nw/9b58bb5e-1d25-4ef6-b787-fb514434adda/6168e9c0-3fc8-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9f4nx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf9f4nw/9b58bb5e-1d25-4ef6-b787-fb514434adda/6168e9c0-3fc8-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9f4nx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 5\"></p>\n<p>Forward path gain : $P_1=G_1, P_2=G_2$</p>\n<p>Individual loop gain : $L_1=-G_1, L_2=-G_2$</p>\n<p>Number of two non-touching loops : 0</p>\n<p>Determinant:</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left[L_1+L_2\\right] \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left[-G_1-G_2\\right] \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1+G_1+G_2 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(i) Path factor:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf9ij4j/2a94b9b8-ca22-4761-87d1-676dbb1c3297/c0024a30-3fc8-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9ij4k.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf9ij4j/2a94b9b8-ca22-4761-87d1-676dbb1c3297/c0024a30-3fc8-11f0-9ed6-a163d15c3250/file-jaoe38c1mbf9ij4k.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 6\"></p>\n<p>All the loops touch forward path $P_1$, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_1=1-\\text { (Isolated loop gain) } \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(ii)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbfev27o/1884bfae-1a35-4da1-b47b-02eac7f59cae/aa1bdb40-3fdd-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbfev27p.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbfev27o/1884bfae-1a35-4da1-b47b-02eac7f59cae/aa1bdb40-3fdd-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbfev27p.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 7\"></p>\n<p>All the loops touch forward path $P_2$, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_2=1-(\\text { Isolated loop gain }) \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_2=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Using Mason's gain formula, transfer function is given by</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1+G_1+G_2} $$</p>\n<p><b>From option (B) :</b></p>\n<p>The given signal flow graph</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbff0h1a/62e53ebf-33a8-4886-986f-3cdb25bfb6d8/409ac5e0-3fde-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbff0h1b.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbff0h1a/62e53ebf-33a8-4886-986f-3cdb25bfb6d8/409ac5e0-3fde-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbff0h1b.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 8\"></p>\n<p>Forward path gain : $P_1=G_1, P_2=G_2$</p>\n<p>Individual loop gain : $L_1=-G_1$</p>\n<p>Number of non-touching loops $=0$</p>\n<p>Determinant:</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left(L_1\\right)=1-\\left(G_1\\right) \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1+G_1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(i) Path factor:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbff3ixa/8bf0bf39-10bb-4d98-91d5-c819fa4ec916/957dbae0-3fde-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbff3ixb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbff3ixa/8bf0bf39-10bb-4d98-91d5-c819fa4ec916/957dbae0-3fde-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbff3ixb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 9\"></p>\n<p>Since, there is no loop, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_1=1-(\\text { Isolated loop }) \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(ii)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbff9e6y/b306d11a-c829-4416-ba44-3d7ef42fc06a/38b0e7a0-3fdf-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbff9e6z.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbff9e6y/b306d11a-c829-4416-ba44-3d7ef42fc06a/38b0e7a0-3fdf-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbff9e6z.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 10\"></p>\n<p>Since, there is no loop, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_1=1-\\text { (Isolated loop) } \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Using mason's gain formula, transfer function is given by,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{P_1 \\Delta_1+P_2 \\Delta_2}{\\Delta} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G_1(1)+G_2(1)}{1+G_1} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1+G_1} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p><b>From option (C) :</b></p>\n<p>The given signal flow graph</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbffbtlz/77d99892-e63a-4a2f-914e-35fb082df566/7c380b70-3fdf-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffbtm0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbffbtlz/77d99892-e63a-4a2f-914e-35fb082df566/7c380b70-3fdf-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffbtm0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 11\"></p>\n<p>Forward path gain : $P_1=G_1, P_2=G_2$</p>\n<p>Individual loop gain : $L_1=G_1, L_2=G_2$</p>\n<p>Number of two non-touching loops : 0</p>\n<p>Determinant:</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left[L_1+L_2\\right] \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1-G_1-G_2 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(i) Path factor :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbffex6m/f97fc62b-b4f5-4bf2-ae1a-a105465a446c/d26819e0-3fdf-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffex6n.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbffex6m/f97fc62b-b4f5-4bf2-ae1a-a105465a446c/d26819e0-3fdf-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffex6n.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 12\"></p>\n<p>All the loops touch forward path $P_1$, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_1=1-\\text { (Isolated loop gain) } \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(ii)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbffqshx/66649f09-a727-4b7e-a8cc-c4e2e92c773b/1c7f1f50-3fe1-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffqshy.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbffqshx/66649f09-a727-4b7e-a8cc-c4e2e92c773b/1c7f1f50-3fe1-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffqshy.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 13\"></p>\n<p>All the loops touch forward path $P_2$, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_2=1-\\text { (Isolated loop gain) } \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_2=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Using Mason's gain formula, transfer function is given by</p>\n<p>$$ \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1-G_1-G_2} $$</p>\n<p><b>From option (D) :</b></p>\n<p>The given signal flow graph</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbfftnti/974172cd-4cb2-4860-96f9-935738f14904/6c4f6760-3fe1-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbfftntj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbfftnti/974172cd-4cb2-4860-96f9-935738f14904/6c4f6760-3fe1-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbfftntj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 14\"></p>\n<p>Forward path gain : $P_1=G_1, P_2=G_2$</p>\n<p>Individual loop gain : $L_1=-G_1, L_2=-G_2$</p>\n<p>Number of two non touching loops : 0</p>\n<p>Determinant :</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left[L_1+L_2\\right] \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1-\\left[-G_1-G_2\\right] \\\\ &amp; \\Delta=1+G_1+G_2 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(i) Path factor:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbffyuxe/25826bef-56eb-4806-8f43-a775ba0439bc/fcd8bf20-3fe1-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffyuxf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbffyuxe/25826bef-56eb-4806-8f43-a775ba0439bc/fcd8bf20-3fe1-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbffyuxf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 15\"></p>\n<p>Since, there is no loop, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_1=1-\\text { (Isolated loop gain) } \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_1=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>(ii)</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbfg1tsg/ca078ecf-2910-4000-8b81-cc23f9bc29b2/4f654100-3fe2-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbfg1tsh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbfg1tsg/ca078ecf-2910-4000-8b81-cc23f9bc29b2/4f654100-3fe2-11f0-9fc7-1b64c8ebfe0c/file-jaoe38c1mbfg1tsh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 2 English Explanation 16\"></p>\n<p>Since, there is no loop, hence</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\Delta_2=1-\\text { (Isolated loop gain) } \\\\ &amp; \\Delta_2=1-0=1 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Using mason's gain formula :</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=T(s)=\\frac{P_1 \\Delta_1+P_2 \\Delta_2}{\\Delta} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=T(s)=\\frac{G_1(1)+G_2(1)}{\\Delta} \\\\ &amp; \\frac{Y(s)}{R(s)}=T(s)=\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1+G_1+G_2} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (B).</p>",
