    "content": "<p>In the following block diagram, R(s) and D(s) are two inputs. The output Y(s) is expressed as Y(s) = G$$_1$$(s)R(s) + G$$_2$$(s)D(s).</p>\n<p>G$$_1$$(s) and G$$_2$$(s) are given by</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyvccicl/53cb6621-b441-42a3-99d9-b5f970204c21/8e684860-4741-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvccicm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyvccicl/53cb6621-b441-42a3-99d9-b5f970204c21/8e684860-4741-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvccicm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 3 English\"></p>",
