    "explanation": "<b>Given :</b>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyvccicl/53cb6621-b441-42a3-99d9-b5f970204c21/8e684860-4741-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvccicm.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyvccicl/53cb6621-b441-42a3-99d9-b5f970204c21/8e684860-4741-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvccicm.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 3 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p>and $Y(s)=G_1(s) R(s)+G_2(s) D(s)$</p>\n\n<p>Let $Y(s)=Y_1(s)+Y_2(s)$</p>\n\n<p>Where, $Y_1(s)=$ Output considering only $R(s), Y_2(s)=$ Output considering only $D(s)$.</p>\n\n<p>When only $R(s)$ is present.</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyvckuc5/324499ab-d602-49e9-a6ce-93b45c6992af/7623dc50-4742-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvckuc6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyvckuc5/324499ab-d602-49e9-a6ce-93b45c6992af/7623dc50-4742-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvckuc6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 3 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{Y_1(s)}{R(s)}=\\frac{\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s) H(s)}}{1+\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s) H(s)}} \\\\\\\\ &amp; Y_1(s)=\\left[\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)+G(s) H(s)}\\right] R(s) \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, $G_1(s)=\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)+G(s) H(s)}$</p>\n\n<p>When only $D(s)$ is present.</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lyvcndp2/7a4ea248-8e2d-4608-ad87-e8bf2a099cce/bcb66b60-4742-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvcndp3.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lyvcndp2/7a4ea248-8e2d-4608-ad87-e8bf2a099cce/bcb66b60-4742-11ef-a981-71ababca86c3/file-jaoe38c1lyvcndp3.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 3 English Explanation 3\">\n\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; \\frac{Y_2(s)}{D(s)}=\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)[1+H(s)]} \\\\\\\\ &amp; Y_2(s)=\\left[\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)[1+H(s)]}\\right] D(s) \\\\\\\\ &amp; \\frac{Y_2(s)}{D(s)}=\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)+G(s) H(s)} \\\\\\\\ &amp; Y_2(s)=\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)+G(s) H(s)} D(s) \\\\\\\\ &amp; G_2(s)=\\frac{G(s)}{1+G(s)+G(s) H(s)} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
