    "content": "<p>The block diagram of a feedback control system is shown in the figure.<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh0ucpxz/11a06576-ab04-4ee6-8900-b1b1029270ef/c8aa4670-aea3-11f0-b8e0-3b25f37f987e/file-jaoe38c1mh0ucpy0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh0ucpxz/11a06576-ab04-4ee6-8900-b1b1029270ef/c8aa4670-aea3-11f0-b8e0-3b25f37f987e/file-jaoe38c1mh0ucpy0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2021 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 1 English\">$$ \\text { The transfer function } \\frac{Y(s)}{X(s)} \\text { of the system is } $$</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>$\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1+G_1 H+G_2 H}$</p>\n"
