    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Converting the given signal into following flow graph</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh0ucp8e/06870cc3-7e2b-4ac9-9fc3-c00cdb1e7398/c81dbde0-aea3-11f0-b8e0-3b25f37f987e/file-jaoe38c1mh0ucp8f.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh0ucp8e/06870cc3-7e2b-4ac9-9fc3-c00cdb1e7398/c81dbde0-aea3-11f0-b8e0-3b25f37f987e/file-jaoe38c1mh0ucp8f.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2021 Control Systems - Signal Flow Graph and Block Diagram Question 1 English Explanation\">From the question,we have</p>\n<p>Forward path-1 Gain $\\Rightarrow G_1 \\Rightarrow P_1$</p>\n<p>Also, Forward path-2 Gain $\\Rightarrow G_2 \\Rightarrow P_2$</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} \\Delta_1 &amp; =1 \\text { and } \\Delta_2=1 \\\\ or,\\Delta &amp; =1-\\left\\{-G_1 H\\right\\}=1+G_1 H \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>On using the Mason Gain formula, we get</p>\n<p>We have Transfer function $=\\frac{1}{\\Delta} \\sum_k P_k \\Delta_k$</p>\n<p>For,&nbsp;&nbsp;$$ K=2 $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}We\\,\\, have\\,\\, \\text { T.F } &amp; =\\frac{1}{1+G_1 H}\\left[G_1+G_2\\right] \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{G_1+G_2}{1+G_1 H} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
